Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
registerTrigger(25.10)                                  registerTrigger(25.10)

Name
       registerTrigger  - Registers the -pre or -post callback procedures with
       the specified commands

Syntax
       registerTrigger

       [-help]

       [{-pre | -post}

       <commandName>

       <procName>]

       Registers the -pre or -post callback procedures with the specified com-
       mands.

       The procedure registered with the -pre parameter runs before the  <com-
       mand_name>  parameter  is used, while the procedure registered with the
       -post parameter runs after the <command_name> parameter is used.

       The arguments passed to <command_name> are passed to  <procedure_name>.
       If  the  procedure registered with the -pre parameter returns a TCL_ER-
       ROR, then <command_name> is not run.

       You can use the registerTrigger  command  after  starting  the  Innovus
       software.

       The registerTrigger command is applicable only for OpenAccess flows.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each registerTrigger parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man registerTrigger.

       -pre   Specifies the procedure to be called before the command.

       -post  Specifies the procedure to be called after the command.

       <commandName>
              Specifies the command name.  The  supported  command  names  are
              saveDesign, restoreDesign, oaIn, and oaOut.

       <procName>
              Specifies  the  procedure name that is to be registered as call-
              back.

Related Information
              * oaIn

              * oaOut

              * restoreDesign

              * saveDesign

